<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Ice Hockey-NHL Rookie-Month,0132 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Kings' Jokinen named NHL rookie of the month
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NEW YORK (AP) _ Los Angeles Kings center Olli Jokinen, who had
four goals and four assists in 11 games in November, was named the
NHL's rookie of the month on Wednesday.
	   Jokinen edged Vancouver Canucks center Bill Muckalt (five goals,
four assists in 14 games) and Pittsburgh Penguins goalie Jean
Sebastien Aubin (3-0-1, 1.76 GAA, one shutout) to win the award.
	   Jokinen recorded points in seven of 11 games last month. He
notched the first multiple-point game of his career with a goal and
an assist in a loss to Calgary on Nov. 10.
	   Jokinen ranks eighth in NHL rookie scoring with eight points. He
was selected third overall by the Kings in the 1997 NHL entry
draft.
</TEXT>
