<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Japan-Economy </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
URGENT
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ The Japanese economy shrank for the fourth straight
quarter, continuing to wallow dangerously in the nation's deepest
recession in decades, the government said Thursday.
	   Japan's gross domestic product _ the measure of all goods and
services produced in the country _ declined by 0.7 percent from
July through September from the previous quarter, the Economic
Planning Agency said.
