<SLUG> BC-Japan-Economy, 1st Add </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TOKYO: Agency said.
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   The agency said the economy contracted at an annual rate of 2.6
percent.
	   Japan has been battered by Asia's financial meltdown, which has
slashed exports, long the mainstay of its economic growth.
	   The economy shrank by 0.8 percent for the April-June period,
compared to the previous quarter. That marked the third straight
quarter of decline and the worst record since the government began
releasing GDP data in 1955.
	   Earlier this year, the government revised its initial estimate
of 1.9 percent growth for this fiscal year ending March 31. It now
says the economy will contract by 1.8 percent.
