<SLUG> BC-Mexico-Gangs,0138 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Mexico City lawmaker surprised by gang number report
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MEXICO CITY (AP) _ Mexico City residents have long known their
city was awash in gangs, but a local legislator has finally tried
to quantify the problem.
	   Some 704 gangs with 18,067 members operate in Mexico's capital,
estimates Soto Camacho, vice president of the city legislature's
Public Safety Commission. He did not cite sources for his figures,
local media said Wednesday.
	   With names like ``The Travoltas,'' ``The Cats'' and ``Los
Jardineros'' _ or ``The Gardeners'' _ one-tenth of the gangs
operate out of high schools and universities preying on fellow
students.
	   Camacho said the school gangs sometimes go beyond their
trademark vandalism and bus hijackings to commit extortion, auto
theft and even murder.
</TEXT>
