	   UNITED NATIONS _ Despite knowing that fighting in Afghanistan
threatens their own security, neighboring nations are still
interfering in and exacerbating the conflict, the U.N. chief says
in a report. UN-AFGHANISTAN. Has moved. By Edith M. Lederer.
	   STOCKHOLM, Sweden _ When the Cold War was at its iciest,
Sweden's military was one of the world's strongest. Now the warming
political climate is melting away its might. SWEDEN-DEFENSE. Has
moved. By Harald Mollerstrom.
	   NEW YORK _ A U.S. investigation of Osama bin Laden led
terrorists to boost their own security in the summer of 1997,
suspecting that a mole was among them, according to a computer
letter apparently written by one of the alleged terrorism kingpin's
aides. US-BOMBINGS-CHARGES. Has moved. By Larry Neumeister.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: Donors conference on reconstruction of war-torn
areas opens in Zagreb, Croatia on Friday.
