<SLUG> BC-Britain-Obit-Burrowes </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Jazz musician Roy Burrowes dies at age 72
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ American jazz musician Roy Burrowes died Wednesday
at age 72.
	   Burrowes, who performed with Duke Ellington and Ella Fitzgerald,
died in St. Thomas's Hospital in London. The cause of death was not
announced.
	   The trumpeter played on numerous Ellington albums including,
``There's a Trumpet in My Soul'' in 1976 and ``Great London
Concerts'' in 1993.
	   Burrowes, who has lived in England for the past eight years,
also worked with his wife, Sandra Noble, to create the
International Jazz Day in Britain.
	   Burrowes was scheduled to take part in a tribute concert to
Ellington in Florida next month.
	   He is survived by his wife and a daughter. Funeral arrangements
were not immediately announced.
	   (mb-rb)
</TEXT>
