<SLUG> BC-Georgia-Anti-Semitism </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Vandals destroy gravestones in Jewish cemetery
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TBILISI, Georgia (AP) _ Vandals knocked over and shattered more
than 50 gravestones at a Jewish cemetery in the Georgian capital
early Thursday, authorities said.
	   No group claimed responsibility for the act, and police said
they were investigating. It was the second such incident at a
Jewish cemetery in Tbilisi in recent years.
	   Georgia's chief rabbi, Ariel Levin, denounced the ``barbarous
act,'' which he said was carried out by someone ``with provocative
goals.''
	   However, he added, ``Nobody will be able to cast a pall over
good and fraternal relations between Georgians and Jews, which have
existed for more than 26 centuries now.''
