<SLUG> BC-Russia-Ethiopia </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russia strikes dlrs 150 million arms deal with Ethiopia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russia will sell fighter jets, combat helicopters
and other military hardware to Ethiopia for dlrs 150 million, a
news agency reported on Thursday.
	   The four Su-27 fighter jets and several Mi-24 and Mi-8 combat
helicopters have been used by the Russian military, but are being
put out of service as part of cuts in the armed forces, the
Interfax news agency reported, quoting military officials.
	   Russia will also provide Ethiopia with ammunition, as well as
communications and navigation equipment, it said.
	   The fighters will fly to Ethiopia on their own, while other
hardware will be airlifted by Russian military transport planes.
All weapons will be delivered later this month, the Interfax said.
	   During Soviet times, Ethiopia was a major recipient of Russian
military hardware.
