<HEADLINE>
Gas explosion kills two people
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; AP Photos

<TEXT>
	   BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) _ An explosion apparently caused by
leaking gas ripped through a building in the capital Thursday,
leaving two dead and seven people severely injured.
	   A 54-year-old woman and her 16 year-old daughter died in the
overnight explosion.
	   Seven people were taken to a hospital with severe burns. Dozens
were left homeless by the blast, which also blew out windows in
neighboring buildings.
	   The leak apparently was located in a laundry on the ground
floor. Radio reports said the owners had been told about the leak
but had taken no action.
