<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Iran-Prison Escape </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Inmates escape from Tehran prison
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TEHRAN, Iran (AP) _ Several inmates were able to escape as they
were being taken from Tehran's notorious Evin Prison to court for
trial, the Tehran Times reported Thursday.
	   It said it had conflicting reports on the number of prisoners
who escaped. It cited a source as saying 11 inmates had managed to
get away earlier this week and another saying less than 11 had
escaped.
	   The paper gave no details as to how the inmates escaped and did
not say if they were political prisoners or common criminals.
	   Prison authorities would not comment on the report.
	   A police hunt in the vicinity of the prison failed to find the
prisoners, the paper said.
	   Evin Prison, which is wedged between steep hills and a suburban
neighborhood in northern Tehran, is believed to be Iran's largest
jail, housing hardened criminals and political prisoners.
 &UR; af-sf
