<HEADLINE>
Car-rich Martina takes first driving lesson
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) _ Martina Hingis, whose tennis ability
has already gained her four cars, has taken her first driving
lesson.
	   Hingis, who turned 18 last Sept. 30 and thus became eligible for
a Swiss driver's license, ventured into traffic for the first time
Wednesday.
	   ``I won't have to depend on somebody else to get around, go
shopping or just go out,'' a smiling Hingis was quoted as telling
the Lausanne daily Le Matin from behind the wheel of her red
hatchback.
	   She has already studied the rules of the road, said her
instructor Walter Frei. ``She's very serious in her attitude toward
driving.''
	   Her only problem on the first day was starting her stick-shift
car uphill, said the mass-circulation Zurich daily Blick.
	   Hingis, who has won two Porsches in tennis tournaments and has
been given two Opels by her sponsor, needs at least a month more in
training before she will be able to take the test and drive them
alone.
