Bank robber takes two customers hostage
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) _ Police were pursuing two armed men who
took two bank employees hostage during a robbery in Lower Saxony
state Thursday and were fleeing with the hostages south toward
Frankfurt.
	   The men, described as heavily armed, threatened to shoot the
hostages if they see any police vehicles along the road, and
demanded that a police helicopter trailing them be pulled back,
police said.
	   Armed with automatic pistols, the men burst into the bank in the
Lower Saxony town of Bad Pyrmont shortly after it opened.
	   It was not immediately clear how much, if any, money they took.
	   Police said they were in contact with the men, but there was no
word on their intended destination or further demands.
