<HEADLINE>
Two Egyptian women, a Jordanian man hanged for murders
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AMMAN, Jordan (AP) _ Two Egyptian maids and a Jordanian man
convicted of murder were hanged at dawn Thursday, a police official
said.
	   Abeer Ibrahim, 24, her 22-year-old sister, Rasha, and Mahmoud
Mashaqba were hanged in their cells at Swaqa Prison, 120 kilometers
(70 miles) southeast of the Jordanian capital, Amman, said the
police official. He spoke on customary condition of anonymity.
	   The Ibrahim sisters had been convicted of murdering their
employer, Fakhria Kurdy, earlier this year. The Egyptian maids tied
Mrs. Kurdy's hands and feet, strangled her to death with a rope and
then stole her money. The official gave no further details.
	   Mashaqba had been convicted of stabbing his neighbor, Mohammad
Zayyoud, with a dagger during a quarrel last year in a parking lot
in the city of Zarqa, 30 kilometers (18 miles) northeast of Amman.
	   Thursday's hanging brings to 10 the total number of people
hanged in Jordan this year _ mostly for serious crimes such as rape
and premeditated murder.
