<HEADLINE>
Attempt to warm heating pipes backfires, burns Russian building
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A man tried to warm the frozen heating pipes in
his apartment complex with a fire, but the blaze quickly spread out
of control and gutted the building, leaving 40 people homeless, a
news report said Thursday.
	   The unidentified man built the fire in the basement of a
two-story wooden building in the Maldyak township in Russia's Far
East, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported.
	   But several rags caught fire and spread the blaze throughout the
building. All the residents managed to escape unharmed, the report
said.
