<HEADLINE>
Gustafsson to play Sanguinetti in opening singles of final
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MILAN, Italy (AP) _ Sweden's No.1 player Magnus Gustafsson was
drawn to play Italy's No.2 Davide Sanguinetti in the opening
singles of the Davis Cup final Friday.
	   In the second singles of the day Italy's top player Andrea
Gaudenzi will be pitted against Magnus Norman as Sweden's
top-ranked player, Thomas Johansson, was not included in the
quartet for the three-day indoor final on clay at Assago Forum.
	   Thursday's draw, in Milan's 16th century city council hall, also
provided Saturday's doubles between the Italian duo of Gaudenzi and
Diego Nargiso against the Swedish pair of Nicklas Kulti and Jonas
Bjorkman.
	   Gaudenzi takes on Gustaffson in a duel between Number Ones in
the reversed singles Sunday wqith Sanguinetti playing Norman.
	   It's the first time in the 99 years of tennis premier team event
that there is no one in the top 30 of the ATP lists playing singles
in the final.
	   Gustaffson is the highlight with No. 31.
	   Italy, which upset the United States in the semifinals, will be
playing its seventh final - the first since 1980 and the first ever
at home.
	   Sweden, a six-time Davis Cup titlist, will be on its 12th final
at Assago.
