w1660 &Cx1f; wstm-
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Sports-Olympics-2002V     12-03 0174
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Olympics-2002 Venues,0176 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Some ice events might swap rinks
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SALT LAKE CITY (AP) _ Salt Lake Olympics planners are
considering switching the sites of some ice events for the 2002
Winter Games.
	   Men's ice hockey could be moved from the E Center in West Valley
City to the Delta Center in Salt Lake City, with figure skating and
short-track speed skating shifting from the Delta Center to the E
Center.
	   Figure skating and short-track speed skating might be better
suited to the E Center because of technical requirements, Salt Lake
Organizing Committee sports director Cathy Priestner Allinger said
Wednesday.
	   ``That doesn't mean we'll change it for sure,'' she said. ``Both
venues know we're revisiting the issue. We have to decide what's
best for the athletes, what's best for the sports.''
	   Delta Center and E Center officials could not be reached for
comment.
	   The decision could hinge on reviews of both venues by
International Skating Union and International Ice Hockey Federation
officials.
</TEXT>
