<HEADLINE>
Bank robbers free one hostage
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with one hostage free &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) _ Two armed men who took two bank
employees hostage during a robbery in Lower Saxony state Thursday
freed one in a Frankfurt suburb, police said.
	   The men, armed with automatic pistols, fled to Frankfurt in a
car belonging to one of the hostages after bursting into the bank
in the Lower Saxony town of Bad Pyrmont shortly after it opened.
	   They threatened to shoot the hostages if they saw any police
vehicles along the road, and demanded that a police helicopter
trailing them be pulled back, police said.
	   It was not immediately clear how much, if any, money they took.
	   Police were talking with the men by mobile telephone for much of
the journey, but lost contact around midday. There was no word on
their intended destination or further demands.
