<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-Davis Cup 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Gustafsson to play Sanguinetti and Gaudenzi takes on Norman in
</HEADLINE>
opening singles &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: CORRECTS that Gaudenzi playing Norman in first match Friday,
ADDS quotes &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MILAN, Italy (AP) _ Sweden's Magnus Gustafsson was drawn
Thursday to play Italy's No. 2 Davide Sanguinetti while Andrea
Gaudenzi will be pitted against Magnus Norman in the opening
singles of the Davis Cup final.
	   Gaudenzi, Italy's top player, will play the inaugural match of
the three-day final against Norman on Friday, as Sweden's
top-ranked player Thomas Johansson was not included in the quartet
for the indoor final on clay at Assago Forum.
	   ``Right now, I have five players on my team who could all play
singles,'' said Swedish team captain Carl-Axel Hageskog. ``From
practice this week it seems like Gustafsson and Norman are the most
ready for this challenge.''
	   The draw, in Milan's 16th century city council hall, also
provided Saturday's doubles between the Italian duo of Gaudenzi and
Diego Nargiso against the Swedish pair of Nicklas Kulti and Jonas
Bjorkman.
	   Gaudenzi takes on Gustafsson in a duel between Number Ones in
the reversed singles Sunday with Sanguinetti playing Norman.
	   It's the first time in the 99 years of tennis' premier team
event that there is no one in the top 30 of the ATP lists playing
singles in the final.
	   Gustafsson is the highest ranked at 31.
	   Italy, which upset the United States in the semifinals, will be
playing its seventh final - the first since 1980 and the first ever
at home.
	   Sweden, a six-time Davis Cup titlist, will be in its 12th final
at Assago.
 &UR; (pv-hjf)
</TEXT>
