<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Teen Suicide Pact </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Five Thai girls fail in joint suicide bid
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ Five teenage schoolgirls in Thailand
drank pesticide during their lunch break Thursday in a failed joint
suicide bid, a local television station reported.
	   The five students, all 13-14 years old, were upset at their
parents for not permitting them to be friends, TV Channel 7 quoted
their teacher as saying.
	   The teacher, Nantha Rangseepanya, said she went to look for the
girls immediately after receiving a tip-off from another student
about their plan.
	   She found them sitting in the school bathroom just moments after
they had consumed the poisonous substance.
	   The students subsequently were admitted to a nearby hospital and
were described as being in serious condition.
	   The police said their investigation had discovered this was just
the latest attempt by the group of students to take their lives,
the report said.
	   News of suicides has attracted widespread attention in Thailand
after the widely publicized death last month of a woman threatening
suicide who fell from a roof after a misguided rescue attempt.
	   The episode, shown repeatedly on television news broadcasts, has
inspired a rash of copycat suicide attempts.	   
</TEXT>
