<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Mine Accident </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ukrainian miner believed killed in accident
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ One Ukrainian miner was feared dead after
he and three more coal workers were flung several hundred meters
(yards) down a shaft by rushing water, officials said Thursday.
	   The accident occurred Tuesday at the Chervony Partyzan mine in
the eastern Luhansk region when a water pipe broke, the Emergency
Situations Ministry said.
	   The four miners were working at the depth of 700 meters (2,310
feet) at the time of the accident. Three were found alive later in
the day after having been driven down an additional 500 meters
(1,650 feet).
	   Rescue workers were still looking for the fourth miner, but he
was feared dead.
	   Ukraine's coal industry has been plagued by accidents at its
aging mines, which lack to money to maintain and upgrade safety
conditions.
	   More than 340 miners have died in mine accidents this year,
including four killed this week at different mines.
	   (vl/gm) 	   
</TEXT>
