<HEADLINE>
New Faroese fisheries minister approinted after predecessor
</HEADLINE>
convicted of rape &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) _ The Faeroe Islands' government on
Thursday appointed Joregen Niclasen as fisheries minister after his
precedessor was convicted last week of raping a teen-age girl.
	   John Petersen admitted having sex with the girl when she was
living in his house three years ago. However, he claimed she
consented and he has appealed the conviction.
	   Niclasen, 29, also is member of Premier Anfinn Kallsberg's
conservative Folkaflokkurin party. The fisheries minister position
is considered a key government post because fish make up 97 percent
of the islands' exports.
	   The Faeroes, an 18-island archipelago midway between Iceland and
Scotland, are Danish territory but have substantial home rule.
	   (jo-jh)
