<SLUG> BC-Bulgaria-NATO </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Bulgaria to host NATO-sponsored 13-nation military exercise
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SOFIA, Bulgaria (AP) _ More than 200 soldiers from 13 nations
will arrive here Friday for NATO-led peacekeeping exercises,
officials said Thursday.
	   During the one-week training, dubbed Cooperative
Determination-98, the soldiers will take part in an exercise to
enforce peace in a mock scenario of an island undergoing natural
disasters and civil war, said Bulgarian Maj. Gen. Kiril Tsvetkov.
	   The operation, on the grounds of the Bulgarian Military Academy,
will include about 220 soldiers from NATO members the United
States, France, Italy and Turkey.
	   It will also include Azerbaijan, Bulgaria, Hungary, Macedonia,
Moldova, Romania, Switzerland, Ukraine and Uzbekistan.
	   The nations are members of Partnership for Peace, a program that
encourages military exercises between NATO and East European
armies.
	   NATO leadership has invited the Czech Republic, Hungary and
Poland to join NATO next year and pledge to consider Bulgaria,
Romania and Slovenia for future membership.
