<HEADLINE>
Nationwide sweep yields two dozen arrests, 3,000 videos seized
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ Dozens of people were detained and 3,000 videos
featuring child pornography were seized in a sweep this week around
France by police trying to crack a pedophilia network, officials
said Thursday.
	   Some two dozen of the 55 people detained on Wednesday were
placed under formal investigation _ one step short of being charged
_ for receiving video cassettes of child pornography, police said.
	   Some 130 investigators took part in the sweep, the latest among
several to crack pedophilia rings. Police coordinated their action
in 34 regions across France.
	   Police said they were acting on a tipoff by one of four men
arrested last year on pedophilia charges. The four men were
arrested in Aveyron, southern France.
