<SLUG> BC-BRF--Russia-Ethiopia,0112 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russia strikes $150 million arms deal with Ethiopia
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: Figures in U.S. dollars

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russia will sell used fighter jets, combat
helicopters and other military hardware to Ethiopia, a news agency
reported today.
	   The $150 million package includes four Su-27 fighter jets and
several Mi-24 and Mi-8 combat helicopters, the Interfax news agency
quoted military officials as saying.
	   Russia also will provide Ethiopia, a close ally of the former
Soviet Union, with ammunition, communications and navigation
equipment, the agency said.
	   The aircraft and other arms will be delivered later this month,
the Interfax said.
</TEXT>
