<HEADLINE>
Last-minute alarm in the cockpit keeps Endeavour grounded
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: NASA news conference scheduled for 6 a.m. EST. &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos &QL; 
 &UR; By MARCIA DUNN &QC; 
 &UR; AP Aerospace Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) _ An alarm went off inside space
shuttle Endeavour's cockpit minutes before today's planned liftoff,
forcing NASA to delay its first space station construction flight.
