before liftoff. But the rain drifted away with minutes to spare and
the clouds were judged by NASA to be scattered and thin enough for
launch _ and then the alarm went off.
	   Secretary of State Madeleine Albright and other dignitaries from
around the world had gathered in the drizzle to see Endeavour and
its crew off following a year's delay caused by a cash crunch in
