<SLUG> BC-GA--Delta Cities,240 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Delta Air Lines to drop service to four cities
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATLANTA (AP) _ Delta Air Lines will discontinue service to three
international destinations and to Bangor, Maine, next year, part of
its continuing effort to concentrate planes on more profitable
routes.
	   Flights to Prague, Czech Republic, which Delta services from New
York via Stuttgart, Germany, will end Jan. 17, the Atlanta-based
airline announced Wednesday.
	   Delta will continue to fly its Stuttgart route and will sell
seats to Prague aboard its codeshare partner, Swissair.
	   On March 2, Delta will end its flights to Bangor, the same day
its commuter affiliate, Comair, begins three daily nonstop flights
from Bangor to Cincinnati with 50-seat regional jets.
	   Delta will stop serving Calgary and Edmonton in Canada on April
4. Commuter affiliate SkyWest will pick up service to Calgary with
three daily flights to its Salt Lake City hub, but not to Edmonton,
the airline said.
	   ``It's the same story,'' Delta spokesman Todd Clay said. ``We've
got greater revenue generation opportunities elsewhere.''
	   As part of its Canadian restructuring, Delta also announced that
it will hire 100 more workers in 1999 at its Montreal reservations
center.
	   Halting its flights to Prague will leave Delta with 22 European
destinations.
	   Domestic destinations Delta has stopped serving this year
include Toledo, Ohio; Fort Wayne, Ind.; Fresno, Calif.; Jackson
Hole, Wyo.; and Idaho Falls, Idaho.
</TEXT>
