<HEADLINE>
Strikes, protests extend across France
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS in 4th graf that many workers fear 35-hour week may lead
to salary cuts &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ Labor unrest continued to mount across France
Thursday, with rail workers still on strike, and jobless protesters
holding sit-ins and even demanding a year-end bonus.
	   The rail strike, which began last Friday, hit 20 out of 23
regions, with services severely disrupted.
	   Rail workers say there is insufficient staff and are concerned
about how the government will implement a plan to cut the working
week from 39 to 35 hours.
	   Many workers fear a 35-hour week, aimed at spreading jobs around
and cutting unemployment, will lead to salary cuts.
