<HEADLINE>
Fire extinguished after raging for 30 hours at Coca-Cola plant
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TIRANA, Albania (AP) - Fireman managed Thursday to put out a
blaze at the Coca-Cola bottling plant which had raged for nearly 30
hours, causing no injuries but considerable damage to one of the
country's major foreign investments.
	   Officials were expected to issue a damage report Friday,
including an estimate of the cost of the blaze.
	   Workers said the fire started early Wednesday after plastic
boxes placed near a huge lamp melted and then ignited the blaze.
	   The four-year-old plant is a joint venture between Atlanta-based
	   Coca-Cola and Italy's Gruppo Busi, which also operates bottling
plants in Italy. The Albanian plant produces about 100 million
bottles annually in a country of fewer than 3 million people.
	   ac/rr
