<HEADLINE>
Turkey president on third visit to Romania in two years
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With AP Photo BUC101,102

<TEXT>
	   BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) _ Turkish President Suleyman Demirel
arrived Thursday for a two-day visit aimed at boosting trade with
this former communist country.
	   In his third official visit to Romania in two years, Demirel
praised good relations with Romania, vowed a rapid increase in
bilateral trade and repeated support for Romania's integration into
NATO and other Western institutions.
	   Romanian President Emil Constantinescu, speaking at Demirel's
side, said he expected trade between the two Balkan countries to
soon reach dlrs one billion yearly from about two-thirds of that
now.
	   Demirel, traveling with Turkish businessmen and academics,
downplayed the collapse last week of Turkey's center-right
government. On Wednesday, veteran politician Bulent Ecevit was
asked to try to form a new administration.
	   ``There is nothing going wrong in Turkey,'' Demirel said.
``Governments can change, this is not new.''
	   Demirel is to inaugurate a Turkish-owned Efes Pilsen beer
factory in Ploiesti, 60 kilometers (38 miles) north of Bucharest.
Some 4,000 Turkish businessmen live in Romania, mostly among the
large Turkish population on the country's Black Sea coast.
	   (mc/am/amb)
