<HEADLINE>
Explosion in Armenian resort kills four children
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   YEREVAN, Armenia (AP) _ An explosion tore through a children's
sanitarium at an Armenian resort on Thursday, killing at least four
children and injuring 12 other people.
	   Investigators believe the mid-afternoon blast may have been
caused by a gas leak, the Emergency Situations Ministry said.
	   The building partially collapsed and rescuers were searching the
rubble for more victims.
	   The sanitarium in Dzhermuk _ a well-known mineral water resort
