<SLUG> BC-Ethiopia-Grant </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Food Program grants Ethiopia dlrs 94.8 million in
</HEADLINE>
aid &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ADDIS ABABA, Ethiopia (AP) _ The U.N. World Food
Program has granted Ethiopia dlrs 94.8 million in
development assistance.
	   In an agreement signed Wednesday between the
government and WFP, dlrs 90.2 million of the grant will be
used to provide 215,817 tons of food assistance. The
remainder, dlrs 4.6 million, will be used for training,
technical equipment, and monitoring and evaluation.
	   ``The agreement provides a framework for community
participation in Ethiopia's development efforts by
allowing individuals and communities to rank their needs
and propose their solutions,'' said WFP country director
Judith Lewis. 
	   The agreement also will provide meals in schools and
aims to alleviate poverty in cities, helping 130,000
primary school students in four regions and 60,000 women
in the capital.
	   ``We want to tackle food insecurity issues before they
reach crisis level,'' said Stephen Anderson, WFP's
development coordinator in Ethiopia.
	   Mulatu Teshome Ethiopian, deputy minister of economic
development and cooperation, said the grant will support
the government's efforts to attain food self-sufficiency,
and to alleviate the chronic poverty in the country.
	   (aa/gm) 
</TEXT>
