<SLUG> BC-Georgia-Anti-Semitism, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Vandals destroy gravestones in Jewish cemetery
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with 60 graves destroyed, president comment. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   TBILISI, Georgia (AP) _ Vandals knocked over and shattered 60
gravestones at a Jewish cemetery in the Georgian capital Thursday,
authorities said.
	   No group claimed responsibility for the act, and police said
they were investigating. It was the second such incident at a
Jewish cemetery in Tbilisi in recent years.
	   Georgia's chief rabbi, Ariel Levin, denounced the ``barbarous
act,'' which he said was carried out by someone ``with provocative
goals.''
	   However, he added, ``Nobody will be able to cast a pall over
good and fraternal relations between Georgians and Jews, which have
existed for more than 26 centuries now.''
	   Georgian President Eduard Shevardnadze echoed the rabbi's words,
saying: For Georgia this is not only inadmissible but is also
unheard of. ... Last fall we celebrated 26 centuries of peaceful
coexistence.''
	   Shevardnadze ordered police to tighten security at the cemetery
and urged a quick, thorough investigation, according to
presidential spokesman Vakhtang Abashidze.
	   (ml/adc)
</TEXT>
