<HEADLINE>
Man arrested in tourist shooting in Barbados
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BRIDGETOWN, Barbados (AP) _ A 26-year-old Barbadian man was
charged in connection with an October hotel shooting that
critically wounded a British tourist, police said Thursday.
	   Darrie Smith, of St. Michael Parish, was arrested Wednesday in
the Oct. 1 shooting of Paula Bridges. Smith faces charges of
shooting with intent to maim, armed robbery, illegal possession of
firearms and possession of marijuana and was to appear before a
magistrate later Thursday.
	   A gun owned by Smith may have been used in the shooting, police
said, adding that more arrests were possible.
	   Bridges, 41, of Suffolk, was shot in the heart during a robbery
at a restaurant bar at Barbados' Palm Court Hotel with her
boyfriend, John Martin. She was hospitalized in critical condition
in Bridgetown before being flown Oct. 11 to James Paget Hospital
near Great Yarmouth, on England's east coast.
	   Martin, 53, was unhurt.
	   The shooting produced an outcry in Barbados, where Attorney
General David Simmons authorized a task force to investigate the
crime.
	   In an effort to curb crimes involving firearms, Barbados
recently increased the penalty for illegal possession of guns from
two years in prison to 20 years.
</TEXT>
