<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   The interaction of a surface high-pressure system over the
Atlantic and a low-pressure system over the eastern Caribbean just
west of the Windward Islands continues to produce the wet and
breezy weather conditions that have been affecting our region for
the past few days.
	   These rainy and windy conditions continue to cause problems,
mainly across the north, east and interior sections of Puerto Rico,
where several watches, warnings and advisories remain in effect.
	   Although the rainy conditions have affected the U.S. Virgin
Islands as well, no problems related to the inclement weather
conditions have been reported.
	   Although the surface winds have diminished somewhat, Doppler
radar as well as upper air observations indicated that winds up to
30 mph continue to affect the highlands of Puerto Rico. For this
reason, a wind advisory continues in effect for the interior
sections of the island.
	   A small craft advisory continues in effect for the coastal
waters of Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands due to the winds
and rough seas. A heavy surf advisory is also in effect for the
north and northeast coasts of Puerto Rico, Culebra, Vieques and the
U.S. Virgin Islands.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Flash flood watch in effect until 4 p.m.
	   Heavy surf advisory in effect.
	   Today... Mostly cloudy and breezy with a 70 percent chance of
showers. Possible thunderstorms. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast 15
to 25 mph with higher gusts.
	   Tonight... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 60 percent
chance of showers. Possible thunderstorms. Low 70 to to 75. Wind
east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Friday... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 50 percent
chance of showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorms. High around
85. Wind east to northeast 15 to 20 mph and gusty.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Flash flood watch in effect until 4 p.m.
	   Heavy surf advisory in effect.
	   Today... Mostly cloudy and windy with a 70 percent chance of
showers. Chance for thunderstorms. High around 80. Wind northeast
15 to 25 mph with frequent higher gusts.
	   Tonight... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 60 percent
chance of showers. Possible thunderstorms. Low 70 to 75. Wind east
10 to 15 mph.
	   Friday... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 50 percent
chance of showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorms. High around
85. Wind east 15 to 20 mph with higher gusts.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Mostly cloudy and breezy with a 50 percent chance of
showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. High around 85. Wind 15
to 20 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy. A 30 percent chance of showers. Low
around 70. Wind northeast 10 mph.
	   Friday... Partly cloudy morning. Increasing cloudiness in the
afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers. Slight chance of a
thunderstorm. High around 85. Wind southeast at 15 mph.
	   Mayaguez and the western regions of Puerto Rico:
	   Heavy surf advisory in effect for Aguadilla.
	   Today... Variable cloudiness and windy with a 60 percent chance
of showers. Slight chance for thunderstorms. High around 85. Wind
northeast 15 to 25 mph with frequent higher gusts.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy. A 30 percent chance of showers. Low
around 70. Wind east to northeast 15 to 20 mph.
	   Friday... Partly cloudy morning. Breezy. Increasing cloudiness
afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers. Slight chance of a
thunderstorm. High around 85. Wind northeast to east 15 to 25 mph.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Flash flood watch in effect until 4 p.m.
	   High wind advisory in effect for higher elevations.
	   Today... Mostly cloudy and windy with a 70 percent chance of
showers. Chance for thunderstorms. High from 70 in the mountains;
80 to 85 in lower elevations. Wind northeast 15 to 25 mph with
higher gusts, 30 to 35 mph in higher elevations.
	   Tonight... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 50 percent
chance of showers. Low 60 to 70. Wind east 15 to 20 mph.
	   Friday... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 50 percent
chance of showers. Chance for thunderstorms. High from 70 in the
mountains; 85 in lower elevations. Wind east 15 to 25 mph and
gusty.
	   St. Thomas, St. John, St. Croix:
	   Heavy surf advisory in effect for north and east coasts.
	   Today... Mostly cloudy and windy with a 70 percent chance of
showers. Chance for thunderstorms. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast 15
to 25 mph and gusty.
	   Tonight... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 60 percent
chance of showers. Possible thunderstorms. Low 70 to 75. Wind east
to northeast 10 to 15 mph and gusty.
	   Friday... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 50 percent
chance of showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. High around 85.
Wind east to northeast 15 to 20 mph and gusty.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Heavy surf advisory in effect.
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   This afternoon... Wind northeast 20 to 30 kt with higher gusts.
Seas 9 to 11 ft in northeast swells. Scattered to numerous showers.
Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind northeast 15 to 25 kt with higher gusts. Seas 7
to 9 ft in northeast swells. Scattered to numerous showers.
	   Friday... Wind northeast 15 to 20 kt with higher gusts. Seas 6
to 8 ft in northeast swells. Scattered showers.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Heavy surf advisory in effect.
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   This afternoon... Wind northeast 15 to 25 kt. Seas 7 to 9 ft in
northeast swells. Scattered to numerous showers. Isolated
thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind northeast 15 to 20 kt. Seas 6 to 8 ft in
northeast swells. Scattered to numerous showers. Isolated
thunderstorms.
	   Friday... Wind northeast 15 kt. Seas 5 to 7 ft. Scattered
showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Near shore waters of western Puerto Rico:
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   This afternoon... Wind northeast 15 to 20 kt. Near shore seas 4
ft. Outer waters seas 4 to 6 ft in north swells. Scattered showers.
Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind northeast 15 to 20 kt. Near shore seas 2 to 4
ft. Outer waters, seas 4 to 6 ft in north swells. Scattered
