<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Nakata </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Manchester United reportedly seeking Japanese star of Perugia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MILAN, Italy (AP) _ Manchester United has made an unsuccessful
28 billion lire (dlrs 16.6 million) bid for Hidetoshi Nakata, the
Japanese star-forward of Italian first division Perugia, Italy's
largest sports daily reported Thursday.
	   Milan's Gazzetta dello Sport wrote that the English Premier
League club has been repeatedly bidding for Nakata in the last few
weeks, getting only refusals from Perugia so far.
	   The young Japanese player is a current sensation in the Italian
Serie A after scoring six goals in 10 league games on his first
season with Perugia.
	   His spectacular overhead kick in last Sunday's match against
Piacenza - the first of his two goals _ was repeatedly shown by
Italian television networks.
	   Perugia officials said several clubs have been seeking Nakata
recently, but declined to comment on Manchester United reported
bid.
	   Gazzetta also reported that negotiations for the transfer of
Internazionale's Nigerian star Nwankwo Kanu to Arsenal have
collapsed at the last minute.
 &UR; (pv)
