<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EU-parliament expenses </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EU parliamentarians agree to review their widely criticized
</HEADLINE>
expenses and salaries &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) _ The European Parliament's legislators
on Thursday decided to streamline their salaries and expenses after
they had come under increasing criticism of public opinion as being
too lavish.
	   A ``common statute'' for members of parliament set their wage at
the average wage of 5.677 Ecus (dlrs 6,580) a month and also
included a decision to bring travel expenses in line with real
costs.
	   Up to now a Spanish parliamentarian received only 2.827 Ecus
(dlrs 3,280) a month, while Italy's legislators topped the list
with 9.635 Ecus (dlrs 11,175). Daily expenses in Brussels stood at
some 9,000 Belgian francs (dlrs 265).
	   European Parliament's total travel bill every year for the 625
parliamentarians from 15 countries costs the taxpayers almost dlrs
30 million.
 &UR; rac
</TEXT>
