<SLUG> BC-Sports-RugbyU-South African Streak </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
With Sports-RugbyU-England-SAfrica
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ South Africa aims to make it a world record 18
wins in a row by beating England at Twickenham on Saturday. Here
are the 17 the Springboks have already won:
	   1997 &QC; 
	   Aug. 23 _ Australia 61-22 at Pretoria.
	   Nov. 8 _ Italy 62-31, Bologna.
	   Nov. 15 _ France 36-32, Lyon.
	   Nov. 22 _ France 52-10, Paris.
	   Nov. 29 _ England 29-11, Twickenham.
	   Dec. 6 _ Scotland 68-10, Edinburgh.
	   1998 &QC; 
	   June 13 _ Ireland 37-13, Bloemfontein.
	   June 20 _ Ireland 33-0, Pretoria.
	   June 27 _ Wales 96-13, Pretoria.
	   July 4 _ England 18-0, Cape Town.
	   July 18 _ Australia 14-13, Perth.
	   July 25 _New Zealand 13-3, Wellington.
	   Aug. 15 _New Zealand 24-23, Durban.
	   Aug. 22 _ Australia 29-15, Johannesburg.
	   Nov. 14 _ Wales 28-20, Wembley.
	   Nov. 21 _ Scotland 35-10, Edinburgh.
	   Nov. 28 _ Ireland 27-13, Dublin.
