<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Germany-Rink </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Leverkusen won't let go Brazilian-born forward to another
</HEADLINE>
Bundesliga club &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LEVERKUSEN, Germany (AP) _ Paulo Rink, the unhappy
Brazilian-born forward of Bayer Leverkusen, won't be allowed to
transfer to another Bundesliga club, but might be able to move
abroad, his club manager said Thursday.
	   Rink, who now has German citizenship, has been benched by
Leverkusen coach Christoph Daum in favor of Ulf Kirsten and Erik
Meijer, a Dutchman.
	   Stuttgart and Hertha Berlin have expressed interest in acquiring
the forward, who is unhappy with sitting on the bench.
	   But Reiner Calmund, the powerful Leverkusen business manager,
ruled out any such transfer to another Bundesliga club.
	   ``If any player says again that he won't sit on the bench, then
he really won't be released, even if we have to take a financial
loss,'' Calmund said.
	   ``If Rink wants to move on at some point, it won't be to Hertha
Berlin or Stuttgart. We have very different financial
possibilities. He would go to southern Europe or Brazil,'' Calmund
said.
	   Rink received German citizenship this summer but his national
team career ended after one game with the resignation of coach
Berti Vogts in September.
	   He has not been considered by new coach Erich Ribbeck and has
not been able to establish himself as a starter in Leverkusen.
	   (ns) 	   
</TEXT>
