<HEADLINE>
Eight workmen fall to death as scaffolding collapses
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BOMBAY, India (AP) _ Eight men were killed in western India when
the iron scaffolding they were working on collapsed Thursday,
doctors said.
	   Firemen rescued 17 others from the debris where the men had been
working on repairs to the 20-story Stirling Apartments, located in
an upscale residential area in downtown Bombay.
	   After several recent building collapses in India's financial
hub, city authorities set up committees to investigate unauthorized
construction and poor building techniques in Bombay.
</TEXT>
