<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-UN-Mitch Aid </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
U.N. appeals for dlrs 153 million in Mitch relief
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   GENEVA (AP) _ The United Nations on Thursday appealed for some
dlrs 153 million to help countries hit by Hurricane Mitch get
through the next six months.
	   The new joint appeal to donors by U.N. agencies is intended to
``tide over'' aid efforts while rebuilding programs for individual
countries are worked out, according to a U.N. statement.
	   Some dlrs 83 million of the money is intended for Honduras and
dlrs 38 million for Nicaragua. The rest will go to El Salvador,
Guatemala and Belize.
	   More than 9,000 people were killed when the hurricane struck a
month ago, most in Honduras. More than a million people were left
homeless.
	   ``There is now an urgent need for humanitarian assistance,
particularly to the poorest, in the form of clean water and food,
shelter, emergency health services, education as well as urgently
needed help in agriculture,'' the U.N. agencies said.
