<BODY>
<SLUG> US-Clinton-Impeachment, 3rd Ld  </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Livingston wants impeachment inquiry ended this month
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: TOPS with news conference &QL; 
 &UR; By LAURIE KELLMAN &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   WASHINGTON (AP) _ Incoming U.S. House Speaker Bob Livingston
said Thursday he hopes the House wraps up its impeachment inquiry
by the end of the month but held out the possibility it could carry
over to the next year unless the Judiciary Committee completes its
work next week.
	   ``I can't say I'd be perfectly happy,'' if that were to happen,
Livingston said during a news conference his Republican colleague
Senate Majority Leader Trent Lott.
	   Livingston said it is too early to make any decision on whether
the House should consider censuring President Bill Clinton as an
alternative to impeachment.
	    &UR; MORE
</TEXT>
