<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Spain-Chariot Dog Race,0178 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Snow-less Spaniards stage dog race
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ZARAGOZA, Spain (AP) _ A dog team race without snow?
	   Yes, 35 mushers and their huskies, malamutes and Samoyeds will
set off Saturday with dog teams pulling four-wheeled carts or
bicycles.
	   The four-day race will take them across 200 kilometers (120
miles) of Los Monegros, a largely flat, semi-desert expanse in the
Aragon region of northeast Spain.
	   ``There are no sleds because there is no snow,'' said Rafael
Arnaiz, a spokesman for the regional tourism office said.
	   There are three categories of teams: carts with six to 12 dogs,
carts with two to five, and bicycles with one to three dogs each.
	   Drivers are limited to a map, a compass and their own instincts.
	   ``The terrain is so uniform that the hardest part is not getting
lost,'' Arnaiz said.
	   The winners in each category will get a ceramic trophy.
	   The Aragon government has staged the race for the last six years
as a promotional event to boost tourism in Los Monegros.
</TEXT>
