<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Tottenham Director </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Director resigns to avoid conflict of interest
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Sam Chisholm resigned Thursday as a director of
Tottenham because of a conflict of interests involving the Premier
League.
	   Chisholm stepped down after being appointed as a consultant to
the Premier League on future television contracts.
	   League rules state that no employee of, nor consultant to, the
Premier League can be a director of a Premier League club.
	   Chisholm was appointed by Spurs before the start of the current
season because of his experience of media issues, particularly in
television. He was formerly a senior figure at Rupert Murdoch's
BSkyB.
	   Chisholm's appointment had already prompted questions from
Manchester United chairman Martin Edwards.
	   League bosses were concerned that Chisholm would be central to
the television talks while still a director of a Premier League
club.
	   (sw)	   
</TEXT>
