<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Dollar-Gold, 2nd Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Dollar slightly lower after European rate cuts, gold down
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: UPDATES late metals rates &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar closed slightly lower in European
trading Thursday, after a brief rally following a round of interest
rate cuts by the 11 countries that will launch Europe's new single
currency next year.
	   Gold was lower.
	   Ten of the 11 countries adopting the euro _ including Germany,
France, and the Netherlands _ dropped their interest rate to 3
percent. Italy dropped to 3.5 percent from 4 percent.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Wednesday:
	   _1.6722 German marks, down from 1.6733
	   _118.76 Japanese yen, down from 120.59
	   _1.3657 Swiss francs, down from 1.3694
	   _5.6062 French francs, down from 5.6102
	   _1.8844 Dutch guilders, down from 1.8857
	   _1,655.8 Italian lire, down from 1,656.50
	   _1.5330 Canadian dollars, down from 1.5362
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6642, up from dlrs
1.6588.
	   Switzerland and Britain are not part of the European currency.
	   Gold closed in London at dlrs 292.70 bid per troy ounce, down
from dlrs 293.70 on Wednesday.
	   In Zurich the bid price was dlrs 292.75, down from dlrs 294.00.
	   Gold fell 90 cents in Hong Kong to dlrs 293.35.
	   Silver opened in London at dlrs 4.74 bid per troy ounce, down
from dlrs 4.77.
	   (rb-acw)
</TEXT>
