<HEADLINE>
Zimbabwe demanding return of Banana after sodomy conviction
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; AP Photo JOH103 &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: LEADS with 2 grafs to RAISE Banana's claim of persecution.
PICKUP 3rd graf pvs. &QL; 
 &UR; By PAT REBER &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) _ A Zimbabwe official said
Thursday that his country would demand the return of a former
president convicted of sodomy after the fugitive, Canaan Banana,
met with President Nelson Mandela in Pretoria.
	   Banana, titular president of Zimbabwe from 1980 to 1987, was
convicted last week of sodomy and homosexual assault. He had been
free on bail and fled Zimbabwe for neighboring Botswana shortly
before his conviction. He pleaded innocent and called the charges
politically motivated.
