<SLUG> BC-Sports-Ice Hockey-Obit-Silver </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Swiss-Canadian ice hockey player Chad Silver dies at 29
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) _ Canadian-Swiss ice hockey player Chad
Silver, who played for the Swiss national team, was found dead in
his Zurich flat Thursday, his club's sports director said. He was
29.
	   Authorities ordered an autopsy, but there was no immediate
information on the cause of death.
	   A statement from his team, the Zurich-based ZSC Lions, said
Silver played in a Swiss league game without problem Tuesday in
Davos and had taken part in training Wednesday.
	   ``When he didn't appear for the warmup Thursday morning, we
found him dead in his bed,'' said the statement.
	   Investigating Judge Daniel Regenmass said there was no
indication of violence. Simon Schenk, club sports director, said
Silver took no drugs and a recent doping test on the player was
negative.
	   Silver, who played junior hockey in his home town of Brandon,
Manitoba, has played the past nine years in Switzerland.
