<SLUG> BC-Armenia-Explosion, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Explosion in Armenian resort kills 4
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with explosion occurring in cafeteria, search dogs
dispatched; CORRECTS that four killed were adults, sted children &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   YEREVAN, Armenia (AP) _ An explosion tore through a cafeteria at
a children's wing of an Armenian resort on Thursday, killing at
least four people and injuring 12 others.
	   Investigators believe the mid-afternoon blast may have been
caused by a gas leak, the Emergency Situations Ministry said.
	   The building partially collapsed and rescuers were searching the
rubble for more victims with the help of search dogs.
	   The children's sanitarium in Dzhermuk _ a well-known mineral
water resort 150 kilometers (90 miles) southeast of Armenia's
capital, Yerevan _ housed children accompanied by their mothers.
	   Forty-two people were in the building at the time of the blast,
though it was unclear how many were in the cafeteria.
	   Armenia's President Robert Kocharian and Prime Minister Armen
Darbinian expressed condolences to the victims' families.
	   (str/ad/adc)
