<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Germany-Balakov </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Bulgarian star gets heavy fine for kneeing opponent
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) _ The German soccer federation Thursday
banned Bulgaria's World Cup star Krasimir Balakov until Jan. 28 for
kneeing Tunisian Zoubaier Baya in a Bundesliga game.
	   Balakov was also fined 40,000 marks (dlrs 24,000) for the
incident that took place last weekend in a game between Balakov's
Stuttgart and Baya's Freiburg, which won 2-0.
	   The incident was missed by the referee but the soccer federation
imposed the ban after seeing television replays.
	   The ban covers a maximum of eight official games and Balakov
will miss the last three Bundesliga games before the winter break
starts Dec. 20.
	   Because the eight-game ban also covers an indoor competition run
by the soccer federation during the break, Balakov should be
available when the Bundesliga resumes Feb. 19.
	   The Bulgarian midfielder is at odds with Stuttgart coach
Winfried Schaefer and was dropped from the German Cup game against
Bayern Munich on Tuesday although he was technically eligible to
play. Stuttgart lost 3-0.
	   (ns) 	   
</TEXT>
