<HEADLINE>
FIFA confirms Zen-Ruffinen as new general secretary
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) _ FIFA's executive committee on
Thursday confirmed Michel Zen-Ruffinen of Switzerland as the world
governing body's new general secretary.
	   He had been acting general secretary since April. His
predecessor, Sepp Blatter, was elected as president of FIFA in
June.
	   Zen-Ruffinen, 39, had been Blatter's deputy since early 1995.
The former international referee and trained lawyer joined FIFA in
1986, taking charge of refereeing matters.
	   He also took over responsibility for legal affairs within FIFA.
	   Zen-Ruffinen, like Blatter, comes from the southern Swiss state
of Valais.
