	   LOD, Israel (AP) _ The United States has received requests that
U.S. President Bill Clinton not land at the newly opened
Palestinian airport during an upcoming visit, a U.S. official said
Thursday.
	   The Clinton administration is considering the Israeli request,
said the U.S. official who spoke on condition of anonymity. The
official said Clinton's travel plans have not yet been finalized.
	   Clinton is to arrive in Israel in the evening of Dec. 12 and on
