<HEADLINE>
Man arrested in tourist shooting in Barbados
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with Smith held without bail, fined for lesser
charges. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BRIDGETOWN, Barbados (AP) _ A 26-year-old Barbadian man was
charged in connection with an October hotel shooting that
critically wounded a British tourist, police said Thursday.
	   Darrie Smith, of St. Michael Parish, was arrested Wednesday in
the Oct. 1 shooting of Paula Bridges. Smith faced charges of
shooting with intent to maim, armed robbery and illegal possession
of firearms and was being held without bail pending a Dec. 10 court
hearing.
	   Magistrate Clyde Nicholls fined Smith dlrs U.S. 2,250 after
Smith pleaded guilty Thursday to marijuana possession and illegally
possessing 16 rounds of ammunition. Smith didn't enter pleas to the
other charges.
