<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Russia-Military, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russian cadet shot after stealing rifle, trying to flee
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES in penultimate graf with criminal case opened against
sentry. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A cadet from a military college in central Siberia
stole a rifle and tried to flee, but was shot to death by a sentry,
a news report said Thursday.
	   Dmitry Filyagin, a third-year cadet in the city of Novosibirsk,
walked into the college's storage area on Wednesday and seized a
rifle from the guard, a fellow cadet, the Interfax news agency
reported.
	   Filyagin then tried to flee, but was stopped by a sentry, who
shot after Filyagin pulled the rifle's breach block, Interfax said.
	   Military officials said the incident may have been a result of
Filyagin's family troubles, Interfax reported. It did not
elaborate.
	   Prosecutors launched criminal proceedings against the sentry,
who is accused of ``exceeding the limits of necessary defense when
detaining a person who has committed a crime,'' the ITAR-Tass news
agency reported, citing the region's deputy military prosecutor,
Lt. Col. Ivan Parnikov.
	   A severe lack of funding and miserable living conditions in the
Russian army have driven scores of servicemen to attack their own
comrades or commit suicide.
	   (ad/gm/adc)
</TEXT>
