Nearly 24,000 killed in car accidents in Russia this year
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Nearly 24,000 people were killed in road accidents
in Russia in January through October this year, and another 132,673
were injured, police said Thursday.
	   The accident rate was 2.1 percent higher then in the same period
last year, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported, citing the country's
chief of traffic police, identified as V. Fyodorov.
	   Fyodorov blamed drunk driving for every fifth car accident,
ITAR-Tass reported.
