<SLUG> BC-NE--Hagel-Russia,165 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Sen. Hagel prepares for foreign relations trip to Russia
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; fonmbmkw1 &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   OMAHA, Neb. (AP) _ Sen. Chuck Hagel plans to spend eight days
next week touring Russia and meeting with the superpower's leaders,
he said Thursday.
	   The Nebraska Republican is scheduled to leave Sunday afternoon
for Siberia and Khakassia, where he'll meet with Gov. Alexy Lebed,
an expected Russian presidential candidate for 2000.
	   Hagel intends to study the country's energy resource platform
and inquire how and where nuclear material from dismantled weapons
is being disposed.
	   ``There's a big concern about the enriched uranium and plutonium
that's coming out of those warheads _ what they're doing with it,
how they're storing it and where they're taking it,'' Hagel said in
a conference call with reporters Thursday.
	   The senator, who chairs the Senate Subcommittee on International
Economic Policy, will also stop in the Baltic country of Lithuania,
which has expressed its interest in joining NATO.
</TEXT>
