<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Nordahl-Obit,0150 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Former Olympic champion dies
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   DEGERFORS, Sweden (AP) _ Bertil Nordahl, the oldest of three
Swedish brothers who starred on the 1948 Olympic champion team in
London, has died. He was 81.
	   One year after winning the Olympic gold, Nordahl signed a
professional contract with Atalanta in Italy. He played in Italy
three years before returning home to the Swedish league. Later, he
became a coach and had stints with Orebro, Brage and Degerfors.
	   Gunnar Nordahl, a powerful high-scoring center-forward for AC
Milan in the 1950s, was the most famous of the three brothers. He
won five season scoring titles with Milan and holds the all-time
record among foreigners with 225 goals.
	   Gunnar Nordahl and Knut Nordahl, the third brother who starred
on the 1948 Olympic team and also later played in Italy, passed
away earlier this decade.
</TEXT>
