<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Germany-Bank Robbery, 3rd Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Bank robbers free hostages
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with three arrested &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) _ Police arrested three men late
Thursday suspected of involvement in a bank heist in Lower Saxony
during which two bank employees were taken hostage but later freed
in a Frankfurt suburb.
	   Two men, armed with automatic pistols, had earlier fled toward
Frankfurt in a car belonging to one of the bank employees after
bursting into the bank in the town of Bad Pyrmont shortly after it
opened.
	   It wasn't immediately clear what role police believe the third
man may have played in the robbery.
	   Police said the men abandoned the car after freeing the
hostages, and fled on foot. Neither hostage was injured.
	   The armed men had threatened to shoot the hostages if they saw
any police vehicles along the road, and demanded that a police
helicopter trailing them be pulled back, police said.
	   It was not immediately clear how much, if any, money they took.
	   Police were talking with the men by mobile telephone for much of
the journey, but lost contact around midday.
	   (cb-dkt)
</TEXT>
