<HEADLINE>
Italy, Lazio star defender returns from World Cup injury
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ROME (AP) _ Italy defender Alessandro Nesta played Thursday for
the first time since tearing knee ligaments at the World Cup,
entering his club Lazio of Rome's Italian Cup game as a substitute.
	   Nesta, 22, joined Lazio's lineup at the start of the second half
against Internazionale of Milan.
	   The center back had been sidelined since June, when he injured
his right knee four minutes into Italy's 2-1 victory over Austria
in first-round play at France '98.
	   Lazio owner Sergio Cragnotti caused an uproar in September when
he announced plans to petition the national soccer federation to
pay compensation for lost services of the player.
