<HEADLINE>
Vandals destroy gravestones in Jewish cemetery
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TBILISI, Georgia (AP) _ Vandals knocked over and shattered more
than 50 gravestones at a Jewish cemetery in the Georgian capital
today, authorities said.
	   No group claimed responsibility for the attack.
	   Georgia's chief rabbi, Ariel Levin, denounced the vandalism as a
``barbarous act'' and said it was carried out by someone ``with
provocative goals.''
	   He added: ``Nobody will be able to cast a pall over good ...
relations between Georgians and Jews, which have existed for more
than 26 centuries.''
