<HEADLINE>
Source: United to trade Gori
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By JOSEPH WHITE &QC; 
 &UR; AP Sports Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   WASHINGTON (AP) _ D.C. United has reached an agreement to send
Mario Gori to the Miami Fusion, a Major League Soccer source said
Thursday.
	   United will likely receive draft picks for the 25-year-old
Argentine defender, according to the source. The trade must be
approved by the league before it is finalized.
	   D.C. United officials did not immediately return phone calls for
comment. The team is in Fort Lauderdale, Florida preparing for
Saturday's Interamerican Cup second-leg match against Brazil's
Vasco da Gama.
	   The deal is the first of many United needs to make stay within
the league's salary cap. Cap restraints also prompted United's
trade of popular forward Raul Diaz Arce to New England earlier this
year.
	   Gori has been with two-time MLS champion United since the team's
inaugural season in 1996, although he has been used sparingly the
last two seasons. This year, he played in 17 games and started nine
with no goals or assists.
	   Gori will remain with United through Saturday's match, the
team's last under coach Bruce Arena. Arena was named coach of the
U.S. national team in October and will be replaced next season by
former Tampa Bay and New England coach Thomas Rongen.
	   Vasco da Gama won the first leg 1-0.
</TEXT>
