<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AP News Digest,0962 </SLUG>


<TEXT>
	   WORLD AT 0000 GMT
	    &UR; NEW:
	   _ TAIWAN-ELECTIONS _ Governing party hopes mayoral candidate
will build support.
	   _ VENEZUELA-CHAVEZ _ Former coup plotter is leading presidential
polls.
	   _ EUROPE-MERGER FEVER _ Cost-cutting gives way to merger wave.
 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   JERUSALEM _ Defying the United States, Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu says he will not back down from a decision to suspend the
Wye River peace agreement over what he calls Palestinian
violations. ISRAEL-PALESTINIANS. RECAP expected by 0300 GMT. By
Samar Assad. AP Photos JRL102-103, 106-108.
	   WITH:
	   _ISRAEL-SOLDIER-DEBATE. Israeli's debate actions of soldier
beaten by Palestinian mob. Has moved.
	   TAIPEI, Taiwan _ The politicians who run Taiwan hope to rebuild
support with a candidate for Taipei mayor who's so squeaky clean he
freely admits spending too much on the campaign. TAIWAN-ELECTIONS.
Expected by 0500 GMT. By Dirk Beveridge AP Photo TPE101.
	   SABANETA, Venezuela _ When he was arrested for trying to
overthrow Venezuela's government in a bloody coup attempt six years
ago, Lt. Col. Hugo Chavez announced to the world his struggle was
just beginning. Now Chavez is the front-runner to become president
days before the election. VENEZUELA-CHAVEZ. Has moved. By Steve
Gutkin. AP Photo CAR106. CAR102
	   MADRID, Spain _ The judge who wants to put former Chilean
dictator Augusto Pinochet on trial is a quiet but relentless sleuth
who has worked for decades tackling drug lords and death squads.
PINOCHET'S PURSUER. Expected by 0100 GMT. By Daniel Woolls. AP
Photo MAD109.
	   UNITED NATIONS _ Iraq has accused U.N. weapons inspectors of
providing enemy intelligence agencies with information obtained
from its searches for weapons of mass destruction. UN-IRAQ. Has
moved. By Edith M. Lederer.
	   WASHINGTON _ Incoming Speaker Bob Livingston wants the full
House called back to vote in December if the Judiciary Committee
approves any articles of impeachment against President Bill
Clinton. US-CLINTON-IMPEACHMENT. Has moved. By David Espo. AP Photo
ACAP102-103, NPT102.
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium _ After a lull over the summer, European
merger fever is returning with a vengeance in a spate of
cross-border link-ups in banking, oil, pharmaceuticals and metals.
EUROPE-MERGER-FEVER. Expected by 0300 GMT. By Paul Ames.
	   WITH:
	   EUROPE-INTEREST RATES. Nations adopting the new European
currency lower key interest rates. RECAP expected by 0300 GMT. By
Didi Kirsten Tatlow. AP Photo FRA102.
	   SAO PAULO, Brazil _ Brazilian lawmakers have failed to pass a
key part of the government's austerity package, signalling growing
public discontent with prescriptions to bolster Brazil's ailing
economy. BRAZIL-ECONOMY. Has moved. By Stan Lehman. SAO101-102.
	   BELFAST, Northern Ireland _ Protestant leader David Trimble says
that he and Catholic politicians appear to have ``cracked''
fundamental problems after talks led by British Prime Minister Tony
Blair. NORTHERN IRELAND. Has moved. By Shawn Pogatchnik. AP Photo
LON118
	   UNITED NATIONS _ The U.N. Security Council blames the renewed
crisis in Angola on the former rebel group UNITA and demands that
it disarm and adhere to a 1994 peace accord. UN-ANGOLA. Has moved.
	   BELGRADE, Yugoslavia _ The Yugoslav Army says it killed eight
ethnic Albanian rebels in what would be the worst violation yet of
a Kosovo cease-fire, and several other armed incidents are reported
Thursday as a U.S. envoy struggles to persuade Serb officials to
accept a peace plan. YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO. Has moved. By Dusan
Stojanovic. AP Photo PRI101.
	   WASHINGTON _ Paintings confiscated from Jews by Nazi Germany,
including works by Picasso and Cezanne, could be returned to prewar
owners or their heirs or auctioned to benefit Holocaust survivors
under guidelines being endorsed Thursday at an international
conference. US-HOLOCAUST CONFERENCE. RECAP expected by 0300 GMT. By
Laura Myers. AP Photos.
	   CAPE CANAVERAL, Florida _ NASA says it will try again Friday to
launch the space shuttle Endeavour, although the weather outlook
was unfavorable for a new flight of NASA's first space station
construction flight. US-SPACE STATION. RECAP expected by 0300 GMT.
By Marcia Dunn. AP Photos KSC107,110.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: Donors conference on war reconstruction opens
Friday in Zagreb, Croatia. Saturday is the third anniversary of the
recapture of Jaffna, Sri Lanka, from ethnic Tamil guerrillas. On
Sunday, national elections scheduled for Gabon.
 &UR; FEATURES:
	   BORSIPPA, Iraq _ After 20 years of digging, Austrian
archaeologists say they've determined the design of a Mesopotamian
ziggurat built by King Nebuchadnezzar about 2,500 years ago.
FEA-IRAQI ZIGGURAT. To move as wire time permits. By Leon Barkho.
AP Photo NY321
	   JAKARTA, Indonesia _ Jakarta's gritty sidewalks are hardly a
place to linger, but street cafes are flourishing _ thanks to
economic hardship. FEA-INDONESIA-CRISIS CAFES. To move as wire time
permits. By Christopher Torchia. AP Photo NY322
	   MEXICO CITY _ Since Mexico's president announced a crusade
against crime and corruption, some progress has been made. But many
believe the system of bribes, construction graft and city-sponsored
protection rackets won't change. FEA-MEXICO-BRIBERY. To move as
