<HEADLINE>
Argentine's Menem visits Toyota Motor Corp.
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ Argentina's President Carlos Menem was scheduled to
visit Toyota Motor Corp. Friday before concluding his four-day trip
to Japan.
	   Menem, who arrived in Tokyo on Tuesday, was to meet Toyota
officials in the morning at the company's headquarters in Nagoya,
269 kilometers (168 miles) west of Tokyo.
	   The Argentinean president met Thursday with Japanese Prime
Minister Keizo Obuchi to discuss bilateral ties.
	   Menem's visit marks the 100th anniversary of the establishment
of formal diplomatic ties between Japan and Argentina.
	   He also had an audience with Japan's Emperor Akihito and Empress
Michiko during his visit. Menem previously visited Japan in 1993.
