<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Rice Record </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Report: Thailand to set rice export record
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ Natural disasters in many producing
countries will help Thailand set a record this year in the export
of rice, a newspaper said Friday.
	   Exports are predicted to hit 6.2 million tons, breaking the
previous record of 6.03 million tons in 1989, the Bangkok Post
quoted Deputy Prime Minister Supachai Panitchpakdi as saying.
	   Thailand exported 5.73 million tons up to the end of last month,
earning 77.6 billion baht (dlrs 1.85 billion).
	   Supachai said natural disasters in countries like Indonesia as
well as a favorable exchange rate for the country's baht currency
had helped increase exports. 	   
</TEXT>
