<HEADLINE>
Fighter jet crashes, killing two
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) _ A Taiwanese fighter jet crashed during a
training flight, killing its two crewmen, the air force said
Friday.
	   The F-5F double-seater went down as the pilot was practicing an
emergency procedure at the Taitung Chih-hang Air Base in
southeastern Taiwan on Thursday, according to a military statement.
	   The jet hit a bunker next to the runway and exploded, officials
said. The cause of the crash was being investigated.
	   The jet was among some 300 F-5 fighters assembled in Taiwan in
the 1980s, using mainly U.S. parts.
</TEXT>
