<HEADLINE>
Reports: China protests flying of Taiwanese flags
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ China has protested the flying of
Taiwanese flags at five venues of the upcoming 13th Asian Games,
newspapers said Friday.
	   The protest was reportedly lodged with the Thai Foreign
Ministry, which later asked organizers of the Games to haul the
flags down.
	   The Nation said the Chinese Embassy had spotted the flags at
several sites including the main stadium for the event, the
athletes village and Bangkok's International Airport.
	   Under an earlier compromise, Taiwan can compete at the Games but
cannot fly its national flag or play its national anthem. Its team
uses a special flag.
	   China is again expected to emerge as Asia's top sports power at
the Games, which begin Sunday.
</TEXT>
