<SLUG> BC-Sports-Ice Hockey-NHL Roundup,0206 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Blackhawks 4, Mighty Ducks 1
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CHICAGO (AP) _ Alex Zhamnov and Chad Kilger scored two goals
each Thursday night and Chicago beat the Anaheim Mighty Ducks 4-1
for their second two-game winning streak this season.
	   Chicago, which managed a pair of shorthanded scores, also ended
a four-game skid against Anaheim, which included two losses this
season. The Mighty Ducks are winless in their last five games
(0-4-1).
	   It was the fifth game of a season-long six-game road trip for
the Mighty Ducks.
 &UR; Senators 3, Kings 1
	   In Kanata, Ontario, Alexei Yashin scored midway through the
third period and Ron Tugnutt made 31 saves to lead the Ottawa
Senators over the Los Angeles Kings.
	   The Kings, playing their third road game in four nights, lost
despite outshooting the Senators 32-18 _ including 13-4 in the
second period. But Tugnutt was spectacular, earning his first
career victory over the Kings in seven decisions.
	   Yashin broke a 1-1 tie when he picked up a loose puck behind the
net, fired a wrist shot from the side of the net which handcuffed
goalie Stephane Fiset and sent him to the ice. Yashin snapped the
rebound over Fiset's shoulder for the game winner.
</TEXT>
