<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Copa Merconorte,0135 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Atletico Nacional advances to final in Copa Merconorte
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MEDELLIN, Colombia (AP) _ In a poorly played game, Atletico
Nacional of Medellin took a giant step towards winning the Copa
Merconorte soccer cup with a 3-1 victory over Deportivo of Cali.
	   Cali's Martin Zapata tied the game at 1-1 with a penalty shot at
the 49-minute mark, but Atletico Nacional responded with goals in
the next 12 minutes by Carlos Andres Vasquez, his second of the
contest, and defender Luis Carlos Perea.
	   The two teams meet again next Wednesday in the second of a
two-game series, however Cali can only take the cup if it wins by a
three goal margin.
	   Thursday's game was played before fewer than 3,000 spectators on
a rainy evening in Atanasio Girardot stadium.
</TEXT>
